noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 shows the result of three root-zone recharge models with the daily precipitation and Makkink (well-watered grass) evaporation of De Bilt as input.
 The bin model has no throttling of the evaporation,
 the earth model has linear throttling when 
\begin_inset Formula $S<Scrit_{R}$
\end_inset

 and the lambda model has throttling of the evaporation according to 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{a}=E\left(\frac{S}{Smax_{R}}\right)^{\lambda}$
\end_inset

.
 The values for 
\begin_inset Formula $Smax_{I}$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $Scrit_{R}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Smax_{R}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

 are given in the header of the figure.
 The top figure shows the original EV24 (Makkink data) and the computed actual evapotranspiration 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{A}$
\end_inset

,
 which,
 of course is the throttled 
\begin_inset Formula $EV24$
\end_inset

.
 The second axes show the precipitation and the actual recharge and the third axes shows the storage of the root zone over time for the three models.
 It's clear that the storage values and,
 therefore,
 the 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{A}$
\end_inset

 and recharge values do not different much between the models.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The models can be run with 
\begin_inset Formula $Smax_{I}=0$
\end_inset

,
 which effectively cancels the interception reservoir.
 Furthermore,
 setting 
\begin_inset Formula $Scrit_{R}=0$
\end_inset

 cancels throttling of the evaporation in the 
\series bold
earth model
\series default
 until the root zone is completely empty,
 making this version of the 
\series bold
earth model
\series default
 behave exactly like the 
\series bold
bin model
\series default
.
 Lastly,
 the 
\begin_inset Formula $Scrit_{R}$
\end_inset

 can be set equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $Smax_{R}$
\end_inset

 which cancels the unrestrained top reservoir of the 
\series bold
earth model
\series default
 making the throttling of the evaporation linear all along the entire root zone,
 which is equivalent to using 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=1$
\end_inset

 in the 
\series bold
lambda model
\series default
.
 Note that the 
\series bold
bin model
\series default
 is equivalent to using 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=0$
\end_inset

 in the 
\series bold
lambda model
\series default
.
\end_layout

